   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1817_02_19_page01.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/>Edgeworthstown
                        <date when="1817-02-19"/>Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> 19, 1817<lb/>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                        My dear <persName ref="./Personography#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Miles</persName>
                  <lb/>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p> I am very much obliged<lb/>
                    to you indeed for having taken<lb/>
                    such trouble about the Crimson<lb/>
                    Shawl - I enclose some letters<lb/>
                    which I received this morning<lb/>
                    &amp; I think that the porter who<lb/>
                    carried it from the hands<lb/>
                    of your messenger to <persName ref="./Personography#CrewX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.<lb/>
                        Crewe</persName>, must have it, or else<lb/>
                    perhaps your messenger.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I think by standing out<lb/>
                    firmly we may obtain some<lb/>
                    tiding from the Porter, who<lb/>
                    I suspect very much - I<lb/>
                    think it was lost between<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_330_1817_02_19_page02.jpg"/> 
                    the door of the Advance<lb/>
                    office &amp; <persName ref="./Personography#CrewX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Crewe</persName> -<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer> 
                 I am dear Madam -<lb/>
                 your obliged &amp; faithful<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography#EdgeM1">Maria <hi rend="underline">Edgeworth</hi>
               </persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>PS. I received your letter<lb/>
                    this morning, but had<lb/>
                    written in the meantime<lb/>
                    to you, a letter which you -<lb/>
                    will receive before this<lb/>
                        Wednesday</p>
            </postscript>
            <closer><!--Use the <closer> element again to hold Address Leaf information.-->plac
                </closer>
         </div>
